parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the exhaust manifold can cause fumes to enter the vehicle, posing a risk to the driver's and passengers' health. Repeated failures can lead to a loss of trust in the vehicle's reliability and safety.
Engine fires can cause damage to the vehicle, pose a risk to the driver's and passengers' safety, and potentially lead to accidents.
Cooling system failures can cause engine overheating, leading to damage, reduced performance, and potentially engine failure.
Poor design and manufacturing can lead to repeated failures, reduced vehicle reliability, and increased maintenance costs.
symptoms: Repeated failures of the same component
A/C lines running directly over the turbo)

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the ignition module can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to potential accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: the ignition module fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty switch assembly can cause a hazardous condition, leading to potential accidents or fires.
symptoms: The switch assembly fails to function
the switch assembly causes an electrical short
the switch assembly leads to a fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery failure and leaks can cause electrical shorts, leading to potential fires or accidents.
symptoms: the battery fails to hold a charge
the battery causes an electrical short
the battery eats through the firewall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hazard light switch can pose a potential danger in emergency situations, such as night-time stops on the highway, where the inability to activate hazard lights can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The hazard light switch becomes brittle and disintegrates
even when used rarely; the switch has a burned appearance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hazard switch can cause the turn signals and hazard lights to stop working, making it difficult for other drivers to see the vehicle, especially at night or on the highway, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The turn signals and hazard lights do not function
the turn signal switch works but the hazard switch does not
the vehicle is not visible to other drivers in low-light conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective gas gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to breakdowns and potentially dangerous situations, especially on highways or at night.
symptoms: The gas gauge reads full when the tank is empty
the vehicle runs out of fuel without warning
the driver is left stranded due to fuel exhaustion.
